ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.255                Enzyme
NAME        mannitol dehydrogenase;
            MTD;
            NAD+-dependent mannitol dehydrogenase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     mannitol:NAD+ 1-oxidoreductase
REACTION    D-mannitol + NAD+ = D-mannose + NADH + H+ [RN:R07135]
ALL_REAC    R07135
SUBSTRATE   D-mannitol [CPD:C00392];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     D-mannose [CPD:C00159];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme from Apium graveolens (celery) oxidizes alditols with a minimum requirement of 2R chirality at the carbon adjacent to the primary carbon undergoing the oxidation. The enzyme is specific for NAD+ and does not use NADP+.
